Proposition 4.7.5 (The case of schemes).
Let X be a scheme, or even algebraic stack, and M âˆˆ Qcoh ( X). Then the following are equivalent:
1. M is dualizable in the sense above.
2. M is locally free of finite rank.
3. M is flat and of finite presentation.
4. If U is an affine scheme which maps to X, then the pullback M|U is associated to a finitely generated projective module.

Dual morphisms: Hom(V,W) = Hom(Wâˆ—âŠ—V, O_C) = Hom(Wâˆ—,Vâˆ—)

Lemma 4.7.9 (Duals invert).
Let Î·:Fâ†’G be a morphism of tensor functors F,G:Câ†’D. If VâˆˆC is dualizable, then Î· ( V) : F ( V) â†’ G ( V) is an isomorphism. In particular, if C is a cocomplete tensor category in which the dualizable objects are colimit-dense, then Hom_câŠ—(C,D) is a groupoid.

