Remark 4.10.2.
In general, the forgetful functor Desc(A) â†’ Mod(A) is faithful and conservative (i.e. reflects isomorphisms). Hence, if A is a descent algebra, then C â†’ Mod(A), M â†’ MâŠ— A is faithful and conservative.

Proposition 4.10.4 (Adjunction).
Assume that C has equalizers. Let A be a commutative algebra in C with unit u : O â†’ A. Then the canonical functor F : C â†’ Desc(A) has a right adjoint G which maps (N,Ï†) to the equalizer of the two morphisms N â†’ A âŠ— N â†’ N âŠ— A, l'un venant de Ï†, l'autre de u.

Proposition 4.10.5 (Faithfully flat descent).
Assume that C has equalizers. Let A be a commutative algebra in C such that 
1. A is a flat object of C.
2. For every MâˆˆC the canonical sequence M â†’ M âŠ— A â‡’ M âŠ— A âŠ— A is exact.
Then A is a descent algebra.
In particular, every faithfully flat commutative algebra is a descent algebra

